User is able to register even after entering more than 30 characters in Email field.
column26:
h3. The user is able to register even after entering more than 30 characters in the Email field.

h3. Steps to reproduce:

h3. 1. Go to the Real Estate website.

h3. 2. Click on the ‘Register’ tab.

h3. 3. Enter an Email address with more than 30 characters.

h3. Expected Result:

h3. The user is not able to register after entering more than 30 characters in the Email field.

h3. Actual Result:

h3. The user is able to register even after entering more than 30 characters in the Email field.

h3. Image where more than 30 characters are entered in the Email fields. 

!email.png|width=1024,height=471!

h3. Image showing registration successful.

!email1.png|width=1024,height=466!

User does not get the LinkedIn login page after clicking on the LinkedIn icon in the 'Blogs' section.
column26:
h3. The user does not get the LinkedIn login page after clicking on the LinkedIn icon in the 'Blogs' section.

h3. Steps to reproduce:

h3. 1. Go to the Real Estate website.

h3. 2. Click on ‘Blogs’ on top of the website.

h3. 3. Click on the LinkedIn icon on that page.

h3. Expected Results:

h3. The user gets to the LinkedIn login page after clicking on the LinkedIn icon in the 'Blogs' section.

h3. Actual Result:

h3. The user does not get the LinkedIn login page after clicking on the LinkedIn icon in the 'Blogs' section.

column1: User is able to register even after entering special characters in First/Last Name field.
column26:
h3. The user is able to register even after entering special characters in the First/Last Name field.

h3. Steps to reproduce: 

h3. 1. Go to the Real Estate website.

h3. 2. Go to the Register tab. 

h3. 3. Enter only special characters in the First and Last Name fields. 

h3. 4. Click on the ‘Register’ button.

h3. Expected Results:

h3. The user is not able to register after entering special characters in the First/Last Name field.

h3. Actual Result:

h3. The user is able to register even after entering special characters in the First/Last Name field. 

h3. Image showing special characters in the First and Last Name field. 

!special characters.png|width=1024,height=470!

h3. Image showing registration is successful even after special characters had been entered in the First and Last Name fields.

!special characters1.png|width=1024,height=467!

column1: User is not automatically logged out of the website if screen is left idle for more than 30 minutes.
column26:
h3. The user is not automatically logged out of the website if the screen is left idle for more than 30 minutes.

h3. Steps to reproduce:

h3. 1. Go to the Real Estate website.

h3. 2. Log in to the website.

h3. Expected Results:

h3. The user is automatically logged out of the website if the screen is left idle for more than 30 minutes.

h3. Actual Result:

h3. The user is not automatically logged out of the website if the screen is left idle for more than 30 minutes.

column1: User is not able to send information in the Contact Us form.
column26:
h3. The user is not able to send information in the Contact Us form.

h3. Steps to reproduce:

h3. 1. Go to the Real Estate website.

h3. 2. Click on the 'Contact Us' link at the bottom of the page.

h3. 3. Enter valid input in the 'Name' field in the Contact form.

h3. 4. Enter valid input in the 'Email' field in the Contact form.

h3. 5. Enter valid input in the 'Subject' field in the Contact form.

h3. 6. Enter valid input in the 'Message' field in the Contact form. 

h3. 7. Click on the ‘Send’ button.

h3. Expected Results:

h3. The user can send information to the team using the Contact Us form.

h3. Actual Result:

h3. The user is not able to send information in the Contact Us form.

!send.png|width=1024,height=468!

!send1.png|width=1022,height=468!

column1: On the 'Real Estate' website, the search bar is not displayed properly.
column26:
h3. The user is not able to see the search bar properly on the ‘Real Estate’ website.

h3. Steps to reproduce:

h3. 1. Go to the Real Estate website.

h3. 2. Click on the 'Real Estate' link at the top of the website and get to that page.

h3. 3. See the search bar.

h3. Expected Results:

h3. The user can see and use the search bar to search for properties.

h3. Actual Result:

h3. The search bar is not positioned properly.

!search.png|width=1024,height=433!

column1: User is not able to find a list of properties in 'Browse Properties' section.
column26:
h3. ‘Browse Properties’ page is not displaying any properties.

h3. Steps to reproduce:

h3. 1. Go to the Real Estate website.

h3. 2. Clicks on the 'Real Estate' link on top of the website and get to that page.

h3. 3. Hover on the 'We help people and homes find each other' link and find a link named 'Browse Properties'.

h3. 4. Click on ‘Browse Properties’ to find a list of properties.

h3. Expected Results:

h3. The user finds a list of properties after clicking on the ‘Browse properties’ link.

h3. Actual Result:

h3. An error page is displayed after clicking on ‘Browse Properties’.

!Browse properties1.png|width=50%!

!Browse properties.png|width=50%!
